-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-05/iran-approves-3-000-candidates-for-march-election-press-tv-says.html
Iran â€™s Guardian Council, the top
legal authority, so far approved some 3,000 candidates to run in
the March 2 parliamentary election,  Press TV  reported, citing
Abbas Ali Kadkhodaei, spokesman for the council.  The candidacy reviews will be completed by Feb. 10,
Kadkhodaei said, according to the state-run news channel. The
Guardian Council, which is composed of jurists and clerics,
reviews candidates to ensure they are suitable to participate in
the election.  Some 5,395 candidates, consisting of 4,967 men and 428
women, registered for the election, interior minister Mostafa
Mohammad-Najjar said on Dec. 30, according to Press TV.  To contact the reporter on this story:
